docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON, May 25 (AP)--Capt. P.G. (Paddy) Dove, who commanded the British tanker Africa Shell in 1939, when she was sunk by the German pocket battleship Graf Spee died at sea today. He was cruising in Indonesian waters with his latest ship, the British tanker Alva Cape.
